{
  "texts": [
    "Training LLMs on more reliable and accurate data reduces the likelihood of LLMs generating hallucinated text.",
    "If users can flag erroneous answers the quality of LLM outputs can improve iteratively.",
    "-Explainability.",
    "Falsehoods are less likely when the LLM is asked to provide references for its claims and statements.",
    "At the very least, the user can then verify the claims them self and potentially factually incorrect sources can be highlighted (Liu N. F. et al., 2023)."
  ]
}